In this article, President Obama pays tribute to Laura Pollán, the founder of Las Damas de Blanco, a group of women in Cuba who peacefully protest against the unjust imprisonment of political dissidents. The president recognizes Pollán's significant contributions to the fight for human rights in Cuba and praises her bravery in the face of repression. He also acknowledges the efforts of the Ladies in White and expresses respect for their dedication to standing up for the rights of the Cuban people, even in the face of recent crackdowns by Cuban authorities. The president reaffirms the United States' support for the Cuban people's desire for freedom and their rights and freedoms as human beings. He also mentions his commitment to supporting civil society in Cuba and ensuring that Cuban Americans can support their families through family visits and remittances.